cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL 

This paper is about a language to specify syntax guided synthesis (SyGuS) problems, which is a prominent theme in contemporary program synthesis approaches. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under programming languages (cs.PL), logic in computer science (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
